dF10FipSnooping.name: dF10FipSnooping

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

dF10FipSnooping.description: The Dell Networking OS Private MIB for FIP Snooping feature. This MIB module is for configuring FIP snooping related objects and monitoring related FCoE sessions. Terminologies used in this MIB are defined by the T11 FCoE standard. Refer to www.t11.org. This MIB also supports configuration of the following objects: - Port role configuration to identify FCF facing or FCF connected interface - FC-MAP value used by the FCF operating in FPMA mode

dF10FIPSAdminMode.name: dF10FIPSAdminMode
dF10FIPSAdminMode.description: This enables or disables FIP Snooping on the system.

dF10FIPSFCMAP.name: dF10FIPSFCMAP
dF10FIPSFCMAP.description: This object configures the FC-MAP value on the system. Default value is 0x0EFC00.

dF10FIPSStatsClear.name: dF10FIPSStatsClear
dF10FIPSStatsClear.description: Clear all FIP Snooping statistics in the system. This is write-only value. It always returns '0' on request.

dF10FIPSVlanCfgTable.name: dF10FIPSVlanCfgTable
dF10FIPSVlanCfgTable.description: A table of the FIP Snooping Vlan configuration entries.

dF10FIPSVlanCfgEntry.name: dF10FIPSVlanCfgEntry
dF10FIPSVlanCfgEntry.description: Represents entry for a FIP Snooping Vlan.

dF10FIPSVlanAdminMode.name: dF10FIPSVlanAdminMode
dF10FIPSVlanAdminMode.description: This enables or disables FIP Snooping on a selected Vlan interface.

dF10FIPSVlanFCMAP.name: dF10FIPSVlanFCMAP
dF10FIPSVlanFCMAP.description: This object configures the FC-MAP value associated with the FIP snooping Vlan. Default value is 0x0EFC00.

dF10FIPSVlanStatsClear.name: dF10FIPSVlanStatsClear
dF10FIPSVlanStatsClear.description: Clear FIP Snooping statistics on this Vlan. This is write-only value. It always returns '0' on request

dF10FIPSIntfEntry.name: dF10FIPSIntfEntry

dF10FIPSIntfPortModeFcf.name: dF10FIPSIntfPortModeFcf

dF10FIPSIntfStatsClear.name: dF10FIPSIntfStatsClear
dF10FIPSIntfStatsClear.description: Clear FIP Snooping statistics on this interface. This is write-only value. It always returns '0' on request

dF10FIPSSessionFCID.name: dF10FIPSSessionFCID
dF10FIPSSessionFCID.description: FCID created by FCF for this virtual session.

dF10FIPSSessionENodeIntf.name: dF10FIPSSessionENodeIntf
dF10FIPSSessionENodeIntf.description: Interface to which the ENode is connected.

dF10FIPSSessionFCFIntf.name: dF10FIPSSessionFCFIntf
dF10FIPSSessionFCFIntf.description: Interface on which the FCF is discovered.

dF10FIPSSessionTime.name: dF10FIPSSessionTime
dF10FIPSSessionTime.description: Time elapsed after this successful virtual session is established by ENode with FCF.

dF10FIPSSessionExpiryTime.name: dF10FIPSSessionExpiryTime
dF10FIPSSessionExpiryTime.description: This is virtual connection/session expiry interval. This is used to monitor the status of the session. Session entry is removed when the value reaches 0. This value is reset to 450 secs (5*90secs) every time an associated VN_Port FKA is received from the ENode. This is ignored (marked as NA) if the D-bit is set to one in the FCF Discovery Advertisements.

dF10FIPSSessionState.name: dF10FIPSSessionState
dF10FIPSSessionState.description: This is the state of the virtual session. The state is displayed as TENTATIVE during the process of ENode login to FCF (using FLOGI or FDESC). It displays ACTIVE after ENode and FCF establish a successful virtual connection.

dF10FIPSFCFVlanIndex.description: FCoE Vlan in which the FCF is present.

dF10FIPSFCFIntf.name: dF10FIPSFCFIntf

dF10FIPSFCFAddressingMode.description: Addressing mode(s) supported by the FCF.

dF10FIPSFCFPriority.name: dF10FIPSFCFPriority
dF10FIPSFCFPriority.description: This is the priority assigned to FCF. The highest priority value is 0 and the lowest priority value is 255.

dF10FIPSFCFDbit.name: dF10FIPSFCFDbit
dF10FIPSFCFDbit.description: This reflects the value of D bit value provided by the most recently received Discovery Advertisement from the FCF.

dF10FIPSFCFIsAvailableForLogin.name: dF10FIPSFCFIsAvailableForLogin
dF10FIPSFCFIsAvailableForLogin.description: This reflects the value of the A bit provided by the most recently received Discovery Advertisement from the FCF. This provides the information that the transmitting FCF is available for FIP FLOGI/FDISC from ENodes. This is informational and shall have no effect on existing logins.

dF10FIPSFCFConfiguredFKA.name: dF10FIPSFCFConfiguredFKA
dF10FIPSFCFConfiguredFKA.description: FIP keepalive interval (FKA_ADV_PERIOD) in seconds configured on the FCF multiplied by five. For example, if the FKA_ADV period configured on the FCF is 80 seconds, the value of this field is 400 seconds.

dF10FIPSFCFTimeSinceDiscovered.name: dF10FIPSFCFTimeSinceDiscovered
dF10FIPSFCFTimeSinceDiscovered.description: Time elapsed since the FCF is discovered.

dF10FIPSFCFConnectedENodesCount.name: dF10FIPSFCFConnectedENodesCount
dF10FIPSFCFConnectedENodesCount.description: Number of ENodes to which FCF has FCoE virtual connections established.

dF10FIPSFCFSessions.name: dF10FIPSFCFSessions
dF10FIPSFCFSessions.description: Total number of FCoE virtual connections successfully established by the ENodes with this FCF.

dF10FIPSFCFExpiryTime.name: dF10FIPSFCFExpiryTime
dF10FIPSFCFExpiryTime.description: This indicates the timer value in seconds to monitor the status of the FCF. FCF entry and all its associated virtual sessions will be removed when the value reaches 0. This value is reset to 'Configured FKA-ADV' every time a Discovery Advertisement is received from the FCF-MAC.

dF10FIPSVlanStatsTable.name: dF10FIPSVlanStatsTable
dF10FIPSVlanStatsTable.description: A table containing per-port, per-VLAN statistics for traffic received. Separate objects are provided for both the most-significant and least-significant bits of statistics counters for ports that are associated with this transparent bridge. The most-significant bit objects are only required on high capacity interfaces, as defined in the conformance clauses for these objects. This mechanism is provided as a way to read 64-bit counters for agents which support only SNMPv1. Note that the reporting of most-significant and least- significant counter bits separately runs the risk of missing an overflow of the lower bits in the interval between sampling. The manager must be aware of this possibility, even within the same varbindlist, when interpreting the results of a request or asynchronous notification.
